org.rappsilber.data.csv

Class CsvParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.rappsilber.data.csv.CsvParser
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    CSVRandomAccess

    public class CsvParser
extends Object
    implements a generic csv-parser, that enables a to access fields by name - including alternatives to these names.
    Author:
    lfischer

      • guessCsv

        public static CsvParser guessCsv(File f,
                                 int guessLines)
                          throws FileNotFoundException,
                                 IOException
        Opens a csv-parser for the given file and tries to predict the quote character and the field-delimiter based on the first number of lines.
        After it reads the first lines it will reopen the file with a configured csv-parser.
        This means, that the file must be re-readable e.g no pipe
        Parameters:
        f - the file to open
        guessLines - how many lines to read in for guessing the parameters
        Returns:
        a CavParser for the file
        Throws:
        FileNotFoundException
        IOException

      • guessCsv

        public static CsvParser guessCsv(File f,
                                 int guessLines,
                                 char[] delimiters,
                                 char[] quotes)
                          throws FileNotFoundException,
                                 IOException
        Opens a csv-parser for the given file and tries to predict the quote character and the field-delimiter based on the first number of lines.
        After it reads the first lines it will reopen the file with a configured csv-parser.
        This means, that the file must be re-readable e.g no pipe
        Parameters:
        f - the file to open
        guessLines - how many lines to read in for guessing the parameters
        delimiters - an array with chars that should be considered as delimiters
        quotes - an array with chars that should be considered as quote-characters
        Returns:
        a CavParser for the file
        Throws:
        FileNotFoundException
        IOException
